{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode\/fsr2","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fsr2"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Case","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15RenderingServerC21ViewportScaling3DModeO4fsr2yA2EmF","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fsr2"}],"title":"RenderingServer.ViewportScaling3DMode.fsr2","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"case"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution 2.2 upscaling for the viewport’s 3D buffer. The amount of scaling can be set using "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale"},{"text":". Values less than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":" will be result in the viewport being upscaled using FSR2. Values greater than ","type":"text"},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are not supported and bilinear downsampling will be used instead. A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":" will use FSR2 at native resolution as a TAA solution.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/viewportscaling3dmode\/fsr2"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","title":"SwiftGodot","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer/ViewportScaling3DMode/fsr2":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/viewportscaling3dmode\/fsr2","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode\/fsr2","title":"RenderingServer.ViewportScaling3DMode.fsr2","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution 2.2 upscaling for the viewport’s 3D buffer. The amount of scaling can be set using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". Values less than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" will be result in the viewport being upscaled using FSR2. Values greater than "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are not supported and bilinear downsampling will be used instead. A value of "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will use FSR2 at native resolution as a TAA solution.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fsr2"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RenderingServer","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"RenderingServer","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Server for anything visible."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RenderingServer","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Viewport/scaling3dScale":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","title":"scaling3dScale","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Scales the 3D render buffer based on the viewport size uses an image filter specified in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/scaling3d\/mode"},{"text":" to scale the output image to the full viewport size. Values lower than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to speed up 3D rendering at the cost of quality (undersampling). Values greater than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" are only valid for bilinear mode and can be used to improve 3D rendering quality at a high performance cost (supersampling). See also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/antiAliasing\/quality\/msaa3d"},{"text":" for multi-sample antialiasing, which is significantly cheaper but only smooths the edges of polygons.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/viewport\/scaling3dscale","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"scaling3dScale"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer/ViewportScaling3DMode":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/viewportscaling3dmode","title":"RenderingServer.ViewportScaling3DMode","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ViewportScaling3DMode"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ViewportScaling3DMode","kind":"identifier"}]}}}